items.text: Just "good cafe" to chill. Inside a little bit noisy, outside rooftop rather cozy. Long black $5.
Btw, the wifi here is really unstable. Don't count on it.
Eggs ben overcooked. Crowded.
Three stories of decent coffee, bean bags, hip decor, fake grass, al fresco seating, swing chairs, and cool dishes. Awesome!
Awesome food and coffee
Very nice and peaceful place to have a relaxing time to drink their TWG tea or coffee, they have 2 levels to seat so you don't have to worry to find a seat if it is not too crowded, I love this place
Hot chocolate is really good, ok price.
Love the poached eggs & mushrooms! More photos at feels.me
It's a good place to chill and relax..
Portobello Eggs Benedict is decent. French toast looks pretty but was tough. Coffee is good. They do soy and also have green tea latte!
The food a a tad expensive for the taste and ambiance. English breakfast set is $16.50, pretty long waiting time. Bread is unique, but everything else is nothing special.
chocolate cheese triplet is a tease. great place for swingers.

Maple seasalt cheesecake is superb! :) Hokkaido milk pudding not fantastic tho :( Also, this place does customized brew (u select ur own beans) & u can name ur personal brew & ask for it agn next time
The classic skillet pancake is yummy... Tastes like a deflated soufflé ... It comes with cream cheese and honey and lemon... Dusted with icing sugar. Makes for a pretty picture and a happy stomach!!
Love the interior - so many great details. Had the eggs benedict and they were fine. But it's too busy with all the students around.
Average food but good coffee. A perfect place to chill :)
I have been there two times and always tried their breakfast. It was my favourite! Recommend this when you want to go cafe hopping!
Food is mediocre.  Ambience is great.
I like the cafe latter taste. It suit my taste milky but it with it coffee smell
Good oyster and shimeji pasta. Nice comfortable environment.
D'good chatty service.
Pretty good tea and a nice place to relax.
Yummy pancake but the yogurt and berry adds to much sourness!!
Very crowded.
Hoshino has better lava cakes than this
Interesting decor and good coffee, but the place was filled with students studying (ie hogging tables for long periods of time)...
I'm a mayor come here and get free coffee from me.  If u cam spot me. 17/4/13
Only average coffee and food. Nice place to chill though. Coffee needs a lot of work before they can brag about it.
Coffee. Service. Pasta. Cute and cosy environment, perfect for couples.
Portions were really small for the price. (And I don't eat a lot) But yummy nonetheless.
Cute coffee art but food was so-so!
Tried the cold brews ~ the white, was sickly and weak... Din taste like coffee. But the Unknown tasted better... Like weak kopi-o with a bitter note.
Step onto the 'grass', take a seat on the swing and watch the world go by ...
Must try their egg benedict !
Cosy interiors with decent coffee good for tête-à-tête. Swings by the windows are the best, with great views out.
Makan time!
The earl-lavender latte is too bland, cold and milky. We also tried the maple sea salt cheesecake and found it average. But I liked their ambience and would like to return to try their mains.
The service staff are super friendly totally not kidding, they recommend you what to eat and they do not rush you just take your time if you need to.
#greatambience
Pancake is soft and nice !
Cozy place, but quite noisy at 3rd floor
Maple Seasalt Cheesecake is the best! Hot chocolate is good! Potato salad is just nice 😊
The aglio olio is horridly dry and cold when served. My cafe latte was cold as well. This place is going onto my blacklist.
i would come here only for 3 things: coffee, free wifi, multiple power plugs. bring earphones or earplugs if u prefer quiet, the space is enclosed so it gets quite noisy when it's crowded.
Pasta was disappointingly mushy
Cosy place to chill.
Great coffee and baked lemongrass chicken. Note: The latter takes half an hour to cook, though.
Took just under an hour for our food to arrive. No apologies, just said they were backed up. Frying bacon ain't rocket science. Organize your kitchen properly!
bacon and tomato sandwich is good
There's wifi here!
They serve all day  breakfast
Good coffee and food. Rooftop rather warm for dining.
Interesting lift. Carbonara pasta good. Iced chocolate and coffee better than many places in SG. Red velvet cake wasn't really fresh though. Recommended place to dine except having cakes.
Decent coffee & sandwich, so many staff, none of whom will take the food to your table
Brunch food is awesome!! But their smoothie...bad and expensive :(
gr8 place 4 a light bite & coffee w friends. interesting cafe layout but well-spaced & nice roof terrace. juices were fresh & pasta was reasonably tasty. staff were honest abt pies being average!
Nice cafe.
I don't usually drink coffee, but I love their coffee mocha! an of course their cakes too!
You have to be early to be able to get a seat of your choice, because people who come here are here to stay. Service is average. Food is average. The tea latte is too rich for my taste.
The coffee. Simply one of the best places - with quality roasted beans with correct flavour profiles unlike most in 🇸🇬.  Should be on the list for any coffee snob from EU/US/AU/NZ. Aeropress,V60 etc
Wifi password is dgoodcafe as of Jan 2015.
Nice waffles and drinks. The ambiance is pretty good and relaxing. Will go again
Carbonara too creamy. Vongole too oily & salty. Would not recommend for food here!
Good ice chocolate. All-day breakfast menu was decent, do check out the popcorn bread with infused hazelnut. Rather cosy ambience for hanging out with friends.
If you are a coffee lover.. Try the v60 or syphlon special... really good. Ask for a recommendation if you are not sure what beans to select.  :)
Nice ambience with a low key setting. Hard to find if you are a newbie. 2nd floor towards the end. Sadly, it opens at 10 am, isn't that late? Hence Starbucks people flock to. Service is passable.
its a 3 floor cafe! 2nd floor for Eames inspired rocking chairs and garden swings and 3rd floor for attic feel- ean bag seatings. Order Rose of Sharan latte for a nice rose flavored coffee!!! 👍❤😆
The ambience is cozy and warm. It has a good vibe. If you are searching for a good spot for catch up, here is the go to place. Stay clear if you want a chill place to hang.
Portobello Eggs Ben nothing to rave about... Eggs used were small and blah... Maybe good if u were on a diet...
Too crowded, no proper queue for seats
Great Ambiance. Cozy, food is pretty tasty as well :)
First visit. Don't like the self-service concept. Especially for lazy ppl like me. I gonna walk up and down at least twice. To make order and collect the foods. Good coffee, foods just normal for me.
do NOT order e TORTUROUS pastas. ordered an aglio olio that was cooked (ages ago) and reheated (it was in the 'food' container!). never again. pls take it off the menu, it is that horrendous!
Awesome place for chillouts. Yet to try their main course. Cute owl is drawn for green tea latte. Friendly staffs.
Had to carry my full cup of matcha latte $7 myself... Feared that it could drop and they had so many wait-staff behind the counter but none offered to help. Too sweet for me.
Great place to chill out. Good food and coffee and cozy ambiance.
Little Diner has better prawn Aglio Olio than this
Baked chicken pesto! Get the table on the second level. It's very cosy.
I did not try the food, but the coffee was rich and non-acidic.
WiFi password is the same as the username
Very nice atmosphere. This cafe tends to serve well for those that like a quiet environment
Yummy eggs Benedict!!
The sandwiches are so tiny!!
